A '''Recreant''' is somehow [[perfidious]] or [[faithless]], when viewed by members of a common [[culture]], who see the Recreant as not persuaded of the common values of the [[society]]. Thus [[defensive behavior]] appears to be a natural reaction by the host society against the Recreants. 

[[Trust]] is thus lacking for a Recreant.

The term appears to be rooted far back in the etymology of [[indo-european]] terminology and stems from the subjective feelings which appear to come to rest in the [[heart]]. See: [[kerd-1]] for this hypothetical root word, which appears to be related to words in Anglo-Saxon and in Latin.

